					<div id=3D"contentSub"><div id=3D"mw-content-subtitle"></div></div>
				=09
				=09
					<div id=3D"mw-content-text" class=3D"mw-body-content"><div class=3D"mw=
-content-ltr mw-parser-output" lang=3D"en" dir=3D"ltr"><div class=3D"shortd=
escription nomobile noexcerpt noprint searchaux" style=3D"display:none">Fel=
ines getting older</div>
<p><b>Aging in cats</b> is the process by which <a href=3D"https://en.wikip=
edia.org/wiki/Cat" title=3D"Cat">cats</a> change over the course of their n=
atural lifespans. The normal lifespan of <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.or=
g/wiki/Cat" title=3D"Cat">domestic cats</a> is in the range of 13 to 20 yea=
rs.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-:02_1-0" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.w=
ikipedia.org/wiki/Aging_in_cats#cite_note-:02-1"><span class=3D"cite-bracke=
t">[</span>1<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> This process, a=
nd different signs will vary from cat to cat depending on different factors=
 such as breed.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-:3_2-0" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"h=
ttps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aging_in_cats#cite_note-:3-2"><span class=3D"c=
ite-bracket">[</span>2<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> Signs=
 of aging may not be predictable but affects all parts of the body, from he=
ad to paw,<sup id=3D"cite_ref-:02_1-1" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https=
://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aging_in_cats#cite_note-:02-1"><span class=3D"cite=
-bracket">[</span>1<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> with fir=
st signs commonly going unnoticed. <sup id=3D"cite_ref-:2_3-0" class=3D"ref=
erence"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aging_in_cats#cite_note-:2=
-3"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>3<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</s=
pan></a></sup>
</p>
<meta property=3D"mw:PageProp/toc">
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading2"><h2 id=3D"Average_lifespan_among_dome=
stic_cats">Average lifespan among domestic cats</h2><span class=3D"mw-edits=
ection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https://e=
n.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DAging_in_cats&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;sec=
tion=3D1" title=3D"Edit section: Average lifespan among domestic cats"><spa=
n>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></di=
v>
<figure typeof=3D"mw:File/Thumb"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/F=
ile:Older_Cat_Jasmine_Close_Up.jpg" class=3D"mw-file-description"><img src=
=3D"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/14/Older_Cat_Jas=
mine_Close_Up.jpg/250px-Older_Cat_Jasmine_Close_Up.jpg" decoding=3D"async" =
width=3D"240" height=3D"319" class=3D"mw-file-element" data-file-width=3D"3=
072" data-file-height=3D"4080"></a><figcaption>This cat is around 18 years =
old; notably, there are specks of grey fur around the eyes.</figcaption></f=
igure>
<p>Reliable information on the lifespans of domestic cats is varied and lim=
ited.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-AnAge2017_4-0" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"http=
s://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aging_in_cats#cite_note-AnAge2017-4"><span class=
=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>4<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> =
Nevertheless, a number of studies have investigated the matter and have com=
e up with noteworthy estimates. Estimates of mean lifespan in these studies=
 range between 13 and 20 years, with a single value in the neighborhood of =
15 years.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-CozziBallarin2017_5-0" class=3D"reference"><a =
href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aging_in_cats#cite_note-CozziBallarin=
2017-5"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>5<span class=3D"cite-bracket">=
]</span></a></sup><sup id=3D"cite_ref-Grimm2015_6-0" class=3D"reference"><a=
 href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aging_in_cats#cite_note-Grimm2015-6"=
><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>6<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span=
></a></sup> At least one study found a median lifespan value of 14 years an=
d a corresponding interquartile range of 9 to 17 years.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-=
O=E2=80=99NeillChurch2014_7-0" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wi=
kipedia.org/wiki/Aging_in_cats#cite_note-O%E2%80%99NeillChurch2014-7"><span=
 class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>7<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a><=
/sup> Maximum lifespan has been estimated at values ranging from 22 to 30 y=
ears although there have been claims of cats living longer than 30 years.<s=
up id=3D"cite_ref-AnAge2017_4-1" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.=
wikipedia.org/wiki/Aging_in_cats#cite_note-AnAge2017-4"><span class=3D"cite=
-bracket">[</span>4<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup><sup id=
=3D"cite_ref-CozziBallarin2017_5-1" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://=
en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aging_in_cats#cite_note-CozziBallarin2017-5"><span cl=
ass=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>5<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></su=
p><sup id=3D"cite_ref-O=E2=80=99NeillChurch2014_7-1" class=3D"reference"><a=
 href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aging_in_cats#cite_note-O%E2%80%99Ne=
illChurch2014-7"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>7<span class=3D"cite-=
bracket">]</span></a></sup><sup id=3D"cite_ref-Arking2006_8-0" class=3D"ref=
erence"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aging_in_cats#cite_note-Ar=
king2006-8"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>8<span class=3D"cite-brack=
et">]</span></a></sup><sup id=3D"cite_ref-Comfort1956_9-0" class=3D"referen=
ce"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aging_in_cats#cite_note-Comfor=
t1956-9"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>9<span class=3D"cite-bracket"=
>]</span></a></sup><sup id=3D"cite_ref-pmid2607740_10-0" class=3D"reference=
"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aging_in_cats#cite_note-pmid2607=
740-10"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>10<span class=3D"cite-bracket"=
>]</span></a></sup><sup id=3D"cite_ref-11" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"h=
ttps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aging_in_cats#cite_note-11"><span class=3D"cit=
e-bracket">[</span>11<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> Accord=
ing to the 2010 edition of the <i><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/=
Guinness_World_Records" title=3D"Guinness World Records">Guinness World Rec=
ords</a></i>, the oldest cat ever recorded was <a href=3D"https://en.wikipe=
dia.org/wiki/Creme_Puff_(cat)" title=3D"Creme Puff (cat)">Creme Puff</a>, w=
ho died in 2005, aged 38 years, 3 days.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-12" class=3D"ref=
erence"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aging_in_cats#cite_note-12=
"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>12<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</sp=
an></a></sup> Female cats typically outlive male cats, and crossbred cats t=
ypically outlive purebred cats.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-CozziBallarin2017_5-2" c=
lass=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aging_in_cats#c=
ite_note-CozziBallarin2017-5"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>5<span c=
lass=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup><sup id=3D"cite_ref-O=E2=80=99Neill=
Church2014_7-2" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wik=
i/Aging_in_cats#cite_note-O%E2%80%99NeillChurch2014-7"><span class=3D"cite-=
bracket">[</span>7<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> It has al=
so been found that the greater a cat's weight, the lower its life expectanc=
y on average.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-O=E2=80=99NeillChurch2014_7-3" class=3D"re=
ference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aging_in_cats#cite_note-O=
%E2%80%99NeillChurch2014-7"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>7<span cla=
ss=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> The current oldest verified cat aliv=
e is <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Flossie_(cat)" title=3D"Floss=
ie (cat)">Flossie</a>, who was born in 1995 in the <a href=3D"https://en.wi=
kipedia.org/wiki/United_Kingdom" title=3D"United Kingdom">United Kingdom</a=
>.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-13" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikiped=
ia.org/wiki/Aging_in_cats#cite_note-13"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</spa=
n>13<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p><p>In one study of cat mortality, the most frequent causes were trauma =
(12.2%), <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Renal_disorder" class=3D"=
mw-redirect" title=3D"Renal disorder">renal disorder</a> (12.1%), non-speci=
fic illness (11.2%), <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Neoplasm" tit=
le=3D"Neoplasm">neoplasia</a> (10.8%) and mass lesion disorders (10.2%).<su=
p id=3D"cite_ref-O=E2=80=99NeillChurch2014_7-4" class=3D"reference"><a href=
=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aging_in_cats#cite_note-O%E2%80%99NeillCh=
urch2014-7"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>7<span class=3D"cite-brack=
et">]</span></a></sup><sup id=3D"cite_ref-:0_14-0" class=3D"reference"><a h=
ref=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aging_in_cats#cite_note-:0-14"><span c=
lass=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>14<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></=
sup>
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading2"><h2 id=3D"Signs_of_aging">Signs of ag=
ing</h2><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracke=
t">[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DAging_in=
_cats&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D2" title=3D"Edit section: Signs of ag=
ing"><span>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></=
span></div>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"Loss_of_senses">Loss of sen=
ses</h3><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracke=
t">[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DAging_in=
_cats&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D3" title=3D"Edit section: Loss of sen=
ses"><span>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></=
span></div>
<p>As a cat ages, it is typical for them to lose the ability to use their s=
enses as they once did. Their sense of smell could decrease as well as thei=
r ability to see. They also could have significant hearing loss, which can =
cause confusion and a change in their vocalizations.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-:3_=
2-1" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aging_in_=
cats#cite_note-:3-2"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>2<span class=3D"c=
ite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>=20
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"Fur">Fur</h3><span class=3D=
"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"=
https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DAging_in_cats&amp;action=3Dedi=
t&amp;section=3D4" title=3D"Edit section: Fur"><span>edit</span></a><span c=
lass=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<p>Fur can become less shiny, duller, and greasier. They may start to get w=
hite/grey fur around their nose, above their upper lip, and in some cases o=
n their back. This change in color can be due to multiple different reasons=
, such as <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cell_hypoxia" class=3D"m=
w-redirect" title=3D"Cell hypoxia">cell hypoxia</a>, hormone changes, and m=
eal changes.  <sup id=3D"cite_ref-:1_15-0" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"h=
ttps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aging_in_cats#cite_note-:1-15"><span class=3D"=
cite-bracket">[</span>15<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"Weight_loss">Weight loss</h=
3><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</=
span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DAging_in_cats&=
amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D5" title=3D"Edit section: Weight loss"><spa=
n>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></di=
v>
<p>Weight loss is common: starting about 2-3 years before a cat dies, they =
may start to lose muscle and <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lean_=
tissue" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Lean tissue">lean tissue</a>. Weighi=
ng cats as they go to the vet is important, so that way their weight can be=
 monitored to predict when aging is starting to take its toll on the animal=
.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-:02_1-2" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wik=
ipedia.org/wiki/Aging_in_cats#cite_note-:02-1"><span class=3D"cite-bracket"=
>[</span>1<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>  One reason for t=
his loss in weight is that, as cats get older, they begin to move around le=
ss, so they don't need to eat as many calories in a day to sustain themselv=
es.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-:02_1-3" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.w=
ikipedia.org/wiki/Aging_in_cats#cite_note-:02-1"><span class=3D"cite-bracke=
t">[</span>1<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>  Their bodies w=
ill also have a harder time digesting food, so they may experience less fat=
 and protein intake from their meals.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-:1_15-1" class=3D"=
reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aging_in_cats#cite_note=
-:1-15"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>15<span class=3D"cite-bracket"=
>]</span></a></sup>
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"Diseases">Diseases</h3><spa=
n class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><=
a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DAging_in_cats&amp;ac=
tion=3Dedit&amp;section=3D6" title=3D"Edit section: Diseases"><span>edit</s=
pan></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<p>Aging cats could have dental disease and the pain caused by this may not=
 stop a cat from eating, but it will prevent the amount that they eat; whic=
h contributes to loss in weight.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-:02_1-4" class=3D"refer=
ence"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aging_in_cats#cite_note-:02-=
1"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>1<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</sp=
an></a></sup> They may begin to lose their teeth if they aren't properly ta=
ken care of, as well as having <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gum=
_disease" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Gum disease">gum disease</a>.<sup =
id=3D"cite_ref-:1_15-2" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia=
.org/wiki/Aging_in_cats#cite_note-:1-15"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</sp=
an>15<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p><p>Other diseases found in cats: <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wi=
ki/Chronic_renal_disease" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Chronic renal dise=
ase">chronic renal disease</a>, <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hy=
perthyroidism" title=3D"Hyperthyroidism">hyperthyroidism</a>, <a href=3D"ht=
tps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Diabetes_in_cats" title=3D"Diabetes in cats">di=
abetes mellitus</a>.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-:02_1-5" class=3D"reference"><a hre=
f=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aging_in_cats#cite_note-:02-1"><span cla=
ss=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>1<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup=
>=20
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"Arthritis">Arthritis</h3><s=
pan class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span=
><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DAging_in_cats&amp;=
action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D7" title=3D"Edit section: Arthritis"><span>edit=
</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<p>Arthritis occurs in the elbows, spines, and shoulders of cats, causing m=
oderate to extreme discomfort. This discomfort can lead to less food intake=
, so it is important that a cat with arthritis has raised bowls and water d=
ishes. <sup id=3D"cite_ref-:02_1-6" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://=
en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aging_in_cats#cite_note-:02-1"><span class=3D"cite-br=
acket">[</span>1<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>=20
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"Nails">Nails</h3><span clas=
s=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href=
=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DAging_in_cats&amp;action=
=3Dedit&amp;section=3D8" title=3D"Edit section: Nails"><span>edit</span></a=
><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<p>Nails become brittle and deformed. <sup id=3D"cite_ref-:1_15-3" class=3D=
"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aging_in_cats#cite_not=
e-:1-15"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>15<span class=3D"cite-bracket=
">]</span></a></sup><sup id=3D"cite_ref-:3_2-2" class=3D"reference"><a href=
=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aging_in_cats#cite_note-:3-2"><span class=
=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>2<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"Skin">Skin</h3><span class=
=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href=
=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DAging_in_cats&amp;action=
=3Dedit&amp;section=3D9" title=3D"Edit section: Skin"><span>edit</span></a>=
<span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<p>Most older cats will get dehydrated skin because they begin to drink and=
 eat less.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-:1_15-4" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https=
://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aging_in_cats#cite_note-:1-15"><span class=3D"cite=
-bracket">[</span>15<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> Flaky s=
kin is also caused when a cat begins to groom less, which is also another c=
ause for oily fur (see "Fur").<sup id=3D"cite_ref-:3_2-3" class=3D"referenc=
e"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aging_in_cats#cite_note-:3-2"><=
span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>2<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span><=
/a></sup>
</p>
